Now, let's start with price delivery cycle. To understand this topic, we must understand the elements required for a price cycle. These are four elements. First one is consolidation, which is also known as range or ranging market. Second one is expansion, its mean a trending condition. Third, retracement or pullback, which is also known as correction. And finally, reversal point which actually indicates the trend reversal. We will study these points one by one in complete details.

Let's start with consolidation. Consolidation is an area where price is moving in a range between two points. You can say consolidation is basically a defined range. Consolidation indicates the lack of a trend in a particular trading range. Its mean there is no clear trend in consolidation phase.
Now question is, what is importance of consolidation? Basically, consolidation is a process of making something stronger, but how this actually benefits us forex market.

Actually, consolidation creates liquidity which is basic need to move market, because most of breakout traders will set their orders on both side of the consolidation or price range. And we know that such pending orders create liquidity.

So, hire the number of orders, hire the liquidity. And if there is a bigger liquidity pool, then market will grab it to make a move a bigger move. That's why we can expect a big move after consolidation.
Let's understand consolidation or trading range by a simple schematic diagram. Here you can see price is ranging between two levels.

Those students who have seen the liquidity concept lecture, they can easily understand that how consolidation creates liquidity. Because breakout traders will set their pending orders on high of this level, and on the lower side of this range.

Now, what is expansion? Expansion is a sign of trend continuation and we know that break of structure is also indicates the trend continuation. Most important things, expansion occurs when price moves quickly after consolidation.

Now, what is its importance in price cycle? Basically, expansion is an indication of smart money footprints. What does it mean? It's mean where it an expansion, it will indicates that smart money is entered at this point. Secondly, we will always look for entry zone near start of expansion. I repeat, the starting zone of expansion will provide us entry zone.

Let's understand it by a simple schematic diagram. This is consolidation phase, which actually used to create liquidity by smart money. When there is large liquidity on either side of this range, market will expand aggressively and quickly. Have you noticed something here? This is liquidity grab or you can call it manipulation by smart money.

Please note, whenever market is in consolidation phase, market will make a big move after that which is expansion. And before expansion, market will try to grab the large liquidity pool on either side of this consolidation or trading range.
So, this can be our entry zone at the start of expansion which is order block or demand zone. I hope now you have complete understanding of expansion and its importance.
Now let's study about retracement. Retracement is basically a pullback within the price range. Please note retracement mostly occurs after expansion which is also known as correction.

Now question is why this is also known as correction? Because correction mean to correct the market cycle, in other words to balance the imbalance price. That's why retracement used to fill the price imbalance and liquidity voids. Please note fair value gap is a refined form of liquidity void and we will cover these entry zones in complete details in next lecture. This is a simple schematic diagram of retracement. As we discussed, retracement mostly occur after expansion.

This is real market sample size. Notice this zone? This is basically a price imbalance. Just for a short note, please note that price imbalance mean where price only moves in one direction. Whenever we will see one sided price move, that area will be marked as price imbalance zone, or we can also market liquidity void.

Now, this is a expansion phase. Right? Now check this gray area, this is basically a retracement that market created to fill this void. Because retracement occurs to balance the imbalance zone. I hope this makes sense to you.
Now let's study about reversal. Reversal is a sign of change of character. A reversal occur when the direction of a price trend has changed, I mean from going up to going down and vice versa.
Now, what is its importance? Reversal gives a advance warning to trend traders, who use to follow trend to design thereby and sell models.

Now, remind a sweep basis change of character model which we have covered in last lecture in complete details. This is a simple schematic diagram of reversal point. Notice that price was bullish and then trend changed to bearish side.
This was large liquidity pool and market sweeped it, grabbed this liquidity and moved into other direction. This is our reversal point.

Now, we have studied all of four elements in complete details. Now, let's study price cycle. For price, these are four main pillars, or you can say four basic elements. Consolidation, expansion, retracement and reversal.

Now question is how the elements actually works in form of cycle? Well, whenever there is consolidation, market will mostly proceed towards an expansion phase. After expansion, market go through the retracement phase to fill the voids. After retracement, a reversal can be occur. And if there is a reversal, market will go through a consolidation phase again.

Now, what we can expect next? First, we can move into a retracement phase. But what if market do not go through retracement, then? Well, in such condition, after expansion market can go to consolidation phase. And after consolidation, market can go to reversal zone.
So, what is summary of this cycle? Basically, price will always moved in this cycle, and these states are interchangeable.

Now, be careful while analyzing the price. Price cannot bypass this cycle, these elements are not directly interlinked. Let me repeat, price cannot bypass this complete cycle. It's mean if market want to adopt any state, it has to follow this cycle and these steps as a natural process.
Please note some abnormality can be seen, but price has to follow this cycle and we will only anticipate market in this cycle.
Similarly, market cannot go to retracement after consolidation, and after retracement, market cannot directly go to consolidation. I hope this make sense to you.
